===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|Sardinia}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|Σαρδώ}}, from its name in a pre-Roman {{etyl|qfa-sub|en}} language, {{m|und|*sard, *shard}}. It is connected by some scholars to the name of the ''{{w|Sherden}}'' or ''Shardana'' {{w|Sea Peoples|Sea People}}. A Phoenician inscription found in {{w|Nora, Italy|Nora}} and dated to the 9th century {{B.C.}} identifies the island as ''shardan''.<ref>''The Cambridge Ancient History'' (ISBN 0521086914), page 369: "In the earliest Phoenician inscription found in Sardinia, that from Nora, probably of the ninth century B.C., although it is incomplete, the name of the island appears as Shardan (be-shardan), [...]"</ref>

